[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *-> [Recipe 8.1: Chief Complaint Classification](chapter08.01-chief-complaint-classification)*
[0m[49m[39m  145, 106[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  146, 107[0m:[39m[49m ## Further Reading
[0m[49m[39m  147, 108[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 148     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - [Clinical Natural Language Processing in Languages Other Than English: Opportunities and Challenges](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jbi.2019.103132) : overview of the state of clinical NLP beyond English
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 149     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - [NegEx: A Simple Algorithm for Identifying Negated Findings](https://doi.org/10.1197/jamia.M1552) : the foundational negation detection algorithm referenced throughout this chapter
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 150     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - [Apache cTAKES](https://ctakes.apache.org/) : the open-source clinical NLP pipeline that pioneered many of the patterns described here
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 151     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - [spaCy](https://spacy.io/) and [medspaCy](https://github.com/medspacy/medspacy) : modern Python NLP libraries with clinical extensions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      109[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [Apache cTAKES](https://ctakes.apache.org/) - the open-source clinical NLP pipeline from Mayo Clinic that implements many of the techniques discussed in this chapter
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      110[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [NegEx Algorithm](https://doi.org/10.1016/S1532-0464(01)00029-6) - Chapman et al.'s foundational 2001 paper on negation detection in clinical text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      111[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [SciSpaCy](https://allenai.github.io/scispacy/) - spaCy models trained on biomedical text, useful for clinical NER and entity linking
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      112[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [UMLS (Unified Medical Language System)](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/index.html) - the NLM's comprehensive biomedical terminology resource that underpins most clinical concept normalization
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      113[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [i2b2/n2c2 NLP Research Datasets](https://portal.dbmi.hms.harvard.edu/projects/n2c2-nlp/) - shared tasks and annotated clinical corpora that have driven clinical NLP research for two decades
